## Adding Icons

Use the `options` prop to customise the tab bar, often with an icon library like `@expo/vector-icons`.

```jsx
import { Ionicons } from '@expo/vector-icons';

<Tab.Screen
  name="Home"
  component={HomeScreen}
  options={{
    tabBarLabel: 'Home',
    tabBarIcon: ({ color, size }) => (
      <Ionicons name="home" color={color} size={size} />
    ),
  }}
/>
```

`color` and `size` are provided by the navigator based on active state.

## Global Configuration

You can also set options on the `Tab.Navigator` itself:

```jsx
<Tab.Navigator
  screenOptions={{
    tabBarActiveTintColor: 'tomato',
    tabBarInactiveTintColor: 'gray',
    tabBarStyle: { backgroundColor: 'white' },
  }}
>
  {/* screens */}
</Tab.Navigator>
```
